# Project Structure Guide

This is a Jekyll-based blog focused on Swift development, iOS development, and Model Context Protocol (MCP) tools.

## Core Configuration
- **Style Guide**: [CLAUDE.md](mdc:CLAUDE.md) - **PRIMARY** content style guide and development commands
- **Main Config**: [_config.yml](mdc:_config.yml) - Site configuration including title, description, navigation, and social links
- **Gemfile**: [Gemfile](mdc:Gemfile) - Ruby dependencies for Jekyll
- **Package.json**: [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Node.js dependencies for build tools (Gulp, SASS, BrowserSync)

## Content Structure
- **Posts**: [_posts/](mdc:_posts/) - Blog posts in Markdown format with YYYY-MM-DD-title.markdown naming
- **Drafts**: [_drafts/](mdc:_drafts/) - Unpublished blog posts
- **Static Pages**: 
  - [index.html](mdc:index.html) - Home page
  - [about.md](mdc:about.md) - About page
  - [articles.md](mdc:articles.md) - Articles listing

## Theme Structure (Long Haul Jekyll Theme)
- **Layouts**: [_layouts/](mdc:_layouts/) - HTML templates for different page types
  - [default.html](mdc:_layouts/default.html) - Base layout
  - [post.html](mdc:_layouts/post.html) - Blog post layout
- **Includes**: [_includes/](mdc:_includes/) - Reusable HTML partials
  - [head.html](mdc:_includes/head.html) - HTML head section
  - [header.html](mdc:_includes/header.html) - Site header
  - [footer.html](mdc:_includes/footer.html) - Site footer
- **SASS**: [_sass/](mdc:_sass/) - Stylesheets organized in modules
  - [_config.scss](mdc:_sass/_config.scss) - SASS configuration and variables

## Assets & Build
- **Assets**: [assets/](mdc:assets/) - Images (`/assets/img/`), videos (`/assets/videos/`), and compiled CSS/JS
- **Scripts**: [_scripts/](mdc:_scripts/) - Python scripts for auto-tweeting posts, includes `tweeted_links.log`
- **Generated**: [_site/](mdc:_site/) - Jekyll-generated static site (ignored in git)

## Key Topics Covered
- Swift development and iOS programming
- XcodeBuild MCP server development
- Swift Package Manager (SPM)
- UI automation with tools like AXe
- MCP (Model Context Protocol) development

## Content Guidelines
- Posts should use front matter with layout, title, date, description, and optional image
- Focus on technical content about Swift, iOS development, and MCP tools
- Include code examples and practical demonstrations
- Use proper markdown formatting with syntax highlighting for Swift code
